  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThe default location for the Prysm data directory on Linux is `$HOME/.eth2` as defined in `cmd/defaults.go`.  \r\nThe XDG Base Directory spec provides standard locations for application data on Linux.  \r\nSee: https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html.  \r\nSee: https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/XDG_Base_Directory.  \r\nIt appears that Prysm does not currently follow this standard.  \r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nPrysm should default to storing its data in `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/eth2` if `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is defined.  \r\nThis may also entail modifying the `FixDefaultDataDir` function in `cmd/defaults.go` to allow users to easily migrate from the old `$HOME/.eth2` to the updated `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/eth2` path.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n",
